Heat the olive oil in a frying pan and gently fry the onion and garlic for 2-3 minutes, or until softened. Stir in the chopped tomato, vinegar and sugar and cook for a further 3-4 minutes, or until the sugar has dissolved.Using a stick blender, process the sauce until smooth, then stir in the cooked tagliatelle and heat through.Transfer the pasta onto a serving plate and garnish with the chopped chives.